    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 632.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your Nos. 627 and 630, of the
                    18th and 24th ultimo, respectively, in relation lo the case of Melcoun
                    Guedjian.</p>
                <p>The Department’s cablegram [of September 26] seems to cover all the essential
                    points in regard to which you ask instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
